article.headline: Sacramento State 68, Portland State 65
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Clark Woods scored 16 to points to lead Sacramento State to a 68-65 win over Portland State on Saturday night. The win snapped a four-game losing streak for the Hornets (5-4, 14-9) and was the first victory for Sacramento State in Portland in 11 tries. Haron Hargrave had 13 points for Sacramento State and DaShawn Freeman added 12 points. Juma Kamara led Portland State (1-8, 8-14) with 15 points and nine rebounds. Anthony Washington added 13 points and Josh Neeley scored 10 points off the bench for the Vikings, who dropped their fifth straight game. With the score tied at 65-65, Alex Bausley connected on a short jumper in the lane to give the Hornets a 67-65 lead with 1:20 left in the game. With 16 seconds remaining, Kamara missed a 3-pointer from the sideline that would have given PSU the lead. Jason Harris iced the game for the Hornets with a free throw with three seconds left to play. Sacramento State shot 44 percent for the game. Portland State connected on 42 percent, but their offense struggled late in the game and scored only two points in the last 6:07 of the game.
